captions.text:
(SINGING) Everything
you do, it sends

me higher than the
moon with everything.
-Hey, guys.

It's Mindy from Cute
Girls Hairstyles.

And today, I am so excited
because it is an amazing today.
Or Bailey would say, "Amazing."

So we are having two, two, two,
two huge announcements for you

in honor of our 250th
video which this one is.
So are you ready?
Because here they come.

Number one is that our app
is finally ready, you guys.

We're so excited for you
guys to be a part of it
and finally get to see it.

So it is ready and available
both on Apple iTunes

if you have an iPhone
like me or on Google Play
if you have an Android device.
It's ready.
You can get it right now.

We have been talking
about doing an app,
I swear, for three years.

And finally, finally,
we've gotten to it.

And it's taken us
like nine months

to develop all the
concepts and build it all.

But it is there and
ready for you guys.

So I know some of you
guys are going to ask,

so I'll answer all your
questions as much as I can.

But yes, there is
a free version.

With the free
version, you're going

to be able to access our last
10 videos anywhere, at anytime,

anyplace, no matter what as
long as you have your iPhone

or one of your mobile
devices with you.

And you can also access
all of our Twitter feed.
It's set up in this cool format.
It's really easy to use.
You're going to love it.

Now, for those of you guys that
want access to the entire 250

video library, we do
have an upgraded version.

It's $0.99 right
now for all of you

guys that are watching for
the next two weeks, $0.99.
So super cheap.

And you guys are
going to love it.
We made it very searchable.

There's lots of different
ways to manipulate

which videos you're watching
which is really cool.

You can even check them
all out by playlists,

so you can look for
difficulty or type

of hair length,
any of that stuff.

Plus, it pulls in all of our
Twitter feed and, best of all,

our Instagram feed
which I love this.

So you can remember
all of those hashtags

we've making you guys use
for the last few months.

All of the CGH, flip
twist braid or whatever

on your hashtags or
your Instagram pictures,

it's going to pull
all of those in.

So if you have more than
50 likes on your picture,
guess who's going to show up?
You guys are.

Which means you're going
to show up on the app.

And we have an actual featured
remember every two weeks.

So it's going to pull up
somebody's amazing cute

little profile picture and
even highlight you guys.

So it's really fun because
you're going to interact.

You're going to get
to meet each other

and see what the other
braid ninjas are doing

and all the other
amazing hair ninjas

that are out there, that
are watching the CGH videos.

And be able to go in and
find their Instagram profiles

and comment on their pictures
and all of that amazing stuff

which is really fun and engages
the whole entire CGH community,

so we all get to give each
other one big giant hug.

And probably, the very
most important feature

of the entire app is
getting early access

to all our weekly videos
so that you can see them

one hour before they
go live on YouTube.

Remember, guys, the
price right now is $0.99.

And in two weeks, two weeks,
that's all you get, $0.99,

and then, the price is
going to go up, so make sure
you go get it right now.

Links are in the
description box below

and also I'll put them
at the end of the video,

so you can make sure and
find them when you need them.
And now, for number two.
So excited for this one.
All right.

Now, you guys know
that we're really

uber-protective of our
children and very careful
about their names.

But two things have
recently happened

that have kind of shifted
our opinion a little bit.

Number one is that
I went down to film

some Mom Views in
California, and I,

of course, filmed with sweet
Colette from the SHAYTARDS.

And as, you know, their kids'
names are very top secret, too,
or were for a while.

And they recently did a name
reveal with their family.

And I got to talking
to her about how

she felt about it, if
she thought it was safe,
if she was glad she had done it.

And she was really,
really positive.

And said everyone was very sweet
and careful with their names
still.
And it has been amazing.

So that made me feel a little
more comfortable with the idea.

Also, it's getting really hard
to keep their name secret.
I mean, we're moving around.
We're doing public appearances.

People are just getting
that information

and starting to share
with each other.

And we kind of wanted to release
their names on our terms.
So today, drum roll, please.
[DRUM ROLL SOUND]
The name release.
Yeah.
-Hi, guys.

We're so excited for
the name release video.
We've waited--
-Yes.

---a long time for you guys
to know our siblings' names.
And now, it's finally here.
So I'm used to be CGH One.
-And I used to be CGH Two.

-But you guys already
know our names

because we have our
own YouTube channel.
-Called BrooklynAndBailey.
-And I'm Brooklyn.
And I'm Bailey.

-And if you aren't watching
our YouTube channel,

there is a link here
for you to describe.

And also, down below
in the description box.

So you should go click on
that so you can our videos.
-You should.
You should.
-You should.

-We do videos like DIYs,
fashion ideas, book reviews.
-Fun exciting stuff.
-Basically, anything.

You could probably
find a video on it.
-Yes.
We're so excited.
So be sure to subscribe.
-Hi, guys.

It's CGH Three or, as
other know me, Special K.

And the reason that they call
me that is because my name is,
wait for it, wait for it, Kamri.

It's said like the car, but
it's spelled differently.
And guess what?

My parents even got me
my own Instagram account.

And you can find
me at KamriNoel.

And I hope to see
you guys all later.
-Hi, guys.

CGH Number Four, and
now, you're going
to know me as RosyNoodleEater.
Just kidding.
My name is Rylan.
Woo hoo.
Woo hoo.
-I'm CGH Five.
But my real name is Daxton.
-I'm CGH Number Six.

I'm Paisley, and
Daxton's my brother.

-One little bonus thing we
wanted to share with you guys

was that we recently received
our gigantic YouTube play

button which is in
honor of us reaching

one million subscribers, which
is just a little bit funny

because we recently hit
two million subscribers.

But I'm so honored and pleased
and excited about receiving
this.

We have a giant wall in
the house ready for it

because every time
we look at this,

we think of all of the
memories and adventures
that we've had with you guys.

And I can't help but
think of the two million

of you that are now
part of our family

and all of the exciting
adventures and memories I hope

to make with you guys for ever
and ever and ever and ever.

So thank you to YouTube
and, more importantly,

thank you to all two
million plus of you.
We love you guys.

And thank you for being
part of our family.

Be sure to come next Sunday
for another amazing hairstyle
tutorial.

And don't forget the
special pricing on the app

is $0.99 right now for
the next two weeks.

Be sure to check
out the links for it

down below or at
the end of video.

And we will see all of
you guys next Sunday.
Bye guys.
(SINGING)
--on the floor.
Happy love is hard to ignore.

When every little thing
you do, I do adore.
Every little thing.
Bu, bu, bu, bu, bu.
Every little thing.
Bu, bu, bu, bu.

Every little thing
you do, I do adore.
